description: Scientists have uncovered the volcanic origin of tiny orange glass beads collected during the Apollo missions. Preserved for over 3.5 billion years, these lava droplets offer crucial insights into the Moon’s fiery past and evolving geology. Advanced analysis now reveals changing volcanic activity and deep interior conditions from the Moon’s formative era.
title: Apollo Astronauts Found Orange Glass Beads on the Moon, Scientists Now Know Why

description: Astronomers have uncovered the universe’s missing baryonic matter using rapid radio bursts. The study, published in Nature Astronomy, shows that most ordinary matter lies between galaxies, hidden in faint intergalactic clouds. This breakthrough highlights FRBs as powerful tools to probe cosmic structures, paving the way for discoveries in large-scale universe mapping and evolution.
title: Fast Radio Bursts Reveal Universe’s Missing Matter Hidden in Cosmic Intergalactic Fog

description: Carbon-dated to 3482–3102 B.C., the Tarkhan Dress is the world’s oldest known tailored garment. Discovered in an Egyptian tomb near Cairo, it offers insights into early textile artistry and everyday life during Egypt’s First Dynasty. Experts believe the linen dress was worn in life before being used in burial, revealing a rare glimpse of ancient fashion.
title: World’s Oldest Tailored Dress Found in Egyptian Tomb Dates Back Over 5,000 Years

description: Aap Jaisa Koi is a soulful romantic drama releasing on Netflix on July 11, 2025. Featuring R Madhavan and Fatima Sana Sheikh, the film explores destiny, love, and second chances through a gentle, emotional lens. Directed by Vivek Soni with music by  Rochak Kohli and Justin Prabhakaran, it's a must-watch love story.
title: Aap Jaisa Koi OTT Release Date: When and Where to Watch Romantic Drama Online?

description: Ancient footprints discovered in White Sands, New Mexico, have been confirmed to be over 23,000 years old, pushing back the timeline of human presence in the Americas by nearly 10,000 years. Radiocarbon dating of mud samples across three labs supports their authenticity, challenging long-held beliefs about the Clovis culture and reshaping early migration theories.
title: Ancient Footprints in White Sands Confirm Humans Reached America 23,000 Years Ago

description: NASA’s Curiosity rover has entered the Uyuni quad on Mars, beginning a new leg of its mission. The rover completed a 48-metre drive and is now collecting fresh data on sedimentary textures and surface chemistry. With a focus on remote sensing and contact science, the team hopes to uncover clues about past Martian environments.
title: Curiosity Rover Reaches Uyuni Quad, Begins New Mars Mapping and Surface Analysis Campaign

description: ESA’s Proba-3 mission has captured the first artificial solar eclipse from space using two satellites flying in precise formation. This breakthrough allows frequent, high-resolution imaging of the sun’s corona, bypassing the rarity of natural eclipses. The mission opens new frontiers in solar physics and space weather research with open access to around 1,000 hours of data.
title: ESA's Proba-3 Unveils First-Ever Artificial Solar Eclipse Images from Precision Satellite Formation

description: The iRonCub3 humanoid robot, developed by Italy’s IIT, has completed its first controlled flight using jet propulsion and AI-powered systems. The 70 kg robot uses neural networks for real-time aerodynamic stability, marking a breakthrough in aerial robotics. Its design enables future use in disaster response, exploration, and hazardous environments where traditional machines cannot operate.
title: Humanoid Robot Achieves Controlled Flight Using Jet Propulsion and AI Systems

description: My Hero Academia returns for its final season in October 2025. With a powerful story, beloved characters, and intense action, this anime has captivated fans globally. Watch it on Crunchyroll, Netflix, or Hulu and witness Midoriya’s ultimate hero journey unfold.
title: My Hero Academia Final Season OTT Release Date Revealed: Everything You Need to Know

description: According to NASA, changes in Earth’s magnetic field 540 million years ago corresponded with atmospheric oxygen shifts. This finding suggests that Earth’s deep interior may impact surface habitability. Scientists plan further research to trace these connections and their role in life’s origin.
title: NASA Study Reveals Correlation Between Earth’s Magnetic Field and Atmospheric Oxygen

description: NASA’s SCIFLI team will track the reentry of a European test capsule named Mission Possible using a spectrometer and high-definition telescope from a Gulfstream III aircraft. The mission aims to gather thermal and parachute deployment data, aiding spacecraft design. Backed by a Space Act Agreement, it highlights international collaboration and enhances safety for future atmospheric entries.
title: NASA to Gather Reentry Imagery of European Commercial Capsule Using High-Altitude Aircraft

description: Capcom has announced a games showcase for next week. The livestream will feature developer interviews and updates on upcoming games like Resident Evil: Requiem and Pragmata. Capcom Spotlight will be livestreamed on June 26.
title: Capcom Spotlight Livestream Announced for Next Week; Will Feature Updates on Resident Evil: Requiem, Pragmata

description: British brand Nothing will launch its Phone 3 on July 1. Ahead of the launch, the brand has confirmed a major design change for the phone. It is teased to come with a Glyph Matrix interface on the back of the device, replacing the previous Glyph interface. The new design could include dot matrix-style lighting on the rear. The Phone 3 will be equipped with the Snapdragon 8s Gen 4 chipset.
title: Nothing Phone 3 to Feature New Glyph Matrix LED Interface on the Rear Panel

description: Honor Magic V5 will be unveiled on July 2 in China. The design of the smartphone was teased during the MWC Shanghai 2025 event. Honor claims that the new phone will be the thinnest and lightest smartphone on the market when launched. The Honor Magic V5 is claimed to provide AI-backed features and 'PC-level productivity'.
title: Honor Magic V5 Set to Launch on July 2, Design Officially Teased

description: OnePlus is said  to be developing a gaming-focused "sub-series" of phones. The device is said to be in the experimental stage, and is expected to feature a flagship chipset, a large battery, and shoulder triggers. A global launch appears unlikely, with its availability likely limited to China, as per the tipster. If unveiled, the phone would compete with phones such as Asus ROG Phone 9 series and the Red Magic 10 Pro lineup.
title: OnePlus Gaming Phone With Flagship Features, Shoulder Triggers Said to Be in Development

description: The Realme Buds Air 7 Pro were recently launched in India. The a truly wireless stereo (TWS) earbud have been introduced in a fiercely competitive price bracket which is characterised by an unprecedented influx of devices.  But do these on-paper upgrades translate into a great real-world auditory experience, or do they disappear in a vast sea of other offerings? Know in our Realme Buds Air 7 Pro review.
title: Realme Buds Air 7 Pro Review: Eye-Catching Design, Thumping Bass

description: The Samsung Galaxy M36 5G will launch in India on June 27 and will be available for purchase via the official website and through Amazon. The phone will be equipped with Google's Gemini AI and Circle to Search features. It will be priced under Rs. 20,000 in the country. The Galaxy M36 5G will sport a 50-megapixel triple rear camera unit with 4K video recording support.
title: Samsung Galaxy M36 5G India Launch Date Set for June 27; Colours, Key Features Revealed

description: Oppo teased the launch of the Reno 14 5G series in the country. While an exact launch date hasn't been revealed, it is confirmed to be available soon. The brand has also posted an image showing the rear design of one of the Reno 14 5G series phones. It is shown in a green shade and a triple rear camera setup.
title: Oppo Reno 14 5G Series India Launch Confirmed: Expected Price, Specifications

description: The Realme 15 series may launch in July, according to a tipster. The lineup will likely include the base model, 15 Pro, and 15 Pro Lite. They are expected to support up to 12GB of RAM and up to 512GB of onboard storage. The base Realme 15 5G handset may get a Snapdragon 7 Gen 4 SoC, a 6,300mAh battery, a 50-megapixel triple rear camera unit, and a 32-megapixel selfie shooter.
title: Realme 15 Series Launch Timeline Leaked; Lite Variant Surfaces Online

description: Apple is interested in tapping generative AI to help speed up the design of the custom chips at the heart of its devices. Johny Srouji, Apple's senior vice president of hardware technologies said Apple needs to use the most cutting-edge tools to design its chips, including the latest chip design software from electronic design automation (EDA) firms.
title: Apple Considering Using AI to Design its Chips, Technology Executive Says

description: Coinbase is launching a platform designed to make stablecoins a go-to payment method for online transactions. The payments initiative could help add new sources of revenue, according to Mark Palmer, analyst at Benchmark.
title: Coinbase Launches Stablecoin Payments Service for E-Commerce

description: Google announced several new features for its Messages app last week, including the ability to snooze notifications and delete text messages for everyone in RCS chats. These capabilities are now rolling out widely to stable users. As the names suggest, the former lets you snooze notifications for incoming messages. Meanwhile, the latter deletes messages for everyone involved in the chat, similar to the existing option on WhatsApp.
title: Google Messages Widely Rolling Out Snooze Notifications and Delete for Everyone Features

description: Nobitex, one of Iran's largest cryptocurrency exchanges, has been hacked for $90 million (roughly Rs. 782 crore). Nobitex’s website was unavailable Wednesday. Messages sent to the company’s support channel on Telegram were not returned.
title: Iran Crypto Exchange Nobitex Hit by Hackers, $90 Million Destroyed

description: Microsoft is planning to axe thousands of jobs particularly in sales. The cuts are expected to be announced early next month, following the end of Microsoft’s fiscal year, according to people familiar with the matter.
title: Microsoft Planning Thousands More Job Cuts Aimed at Salespeople

description: Microsoft is prepared to abandon its high-stakes negotiations with OpenAI over the future of its alliance. OpenAI requires approval from Microsoft, its major backer, to complete its transition into a public-benefit corporation.
title: Microsoft Said to Be Prepared to Abandon High-Stakes Talks with OpenAI

description: OnePlus Bullets Wireless Z3 were launched in India at Rs. 1,699 and will be available for purchase via the official online and offline stores, Amazon, Flipkart, Myntra, and select retail stores starting June 24. The neckband-style wireless earphones feature 12.4mm dynamic bass drivers, magnetic earbuds, and an IP55-rated build. On a single charge, the Bullets Wireless Z3 are claimed to offer a playback of up to 36 hours.
title: OnePlus Bullets Wireless Z3 With 12.4mm Drivers, Up to 36 Hours of Battery Life Launched in India

description: Vivo T4 Lite 5G is all set to launch in India on June 24. It is confirmed to be powered by a MediaTek Dimensity 6300 chipset alongside up to 2 TB of expandable storage. The phone will have a 6.74-inch display and will be available for purchase through Flipkart, Vivo India website, and select retail stores.
title: Vivo T4 Lite 5G India Launch Date Announced; to Feature MediaTek Dimensity 6300 SoC

description: Vodafone Idea (Vi) on Wednesday announced a strategic partnership with US-based satellite technology company AST SpaceMobile to introduce direct-to-device  satellite broadband connectivity in India. With this move, the telecommunications provider aims to expand broadband-based cellular access at locations with challenging terrains where deployment of terrestrial infrastructure is difficult.
title: Vodafone Idea Partners With AST SpaceMobile to Bring Direct-to-Device Satellite Connectivity to India

description: Apple supplier Foxconn will reportedly start the production of the iPhone Fold by the end of the third quarter or early in the fourth quarter of this year. Apple is yet to finalise several component specifications, including the hinge, as per a report. Previous rumours point to a fall 2026 launch for Apple’s foldable iPhone. However, the plans could change before the project officially begins.
title: Apple's Foldable iPhone to Enter Production Later This Year, Components Not Finalised: Ming-Chi Kuo

description: Google on Wednesday rolled out Search Live in AI Mode as part of a small experiment in the US. This feature lets users have back-and-forth conversations in real-time in Search, similar to Gemini Live but in the Google app. It was first announced during the Mountain View-based tech giant’s I/O 2025 keynote session in May as an extension to the AI Mode. Search Live is powered by a custom version of Gemini and has voice input capabilities, enabling the ability to not just ask queries, but also follow-up questions.
title: Google App Gets Gemini-Powered Search Live Feature in AI Mode With Voice Input Support

description: After successful launches on PS5 and PC, Stellar Blade could be coming to Nintendo Switch 2. Developer Shift Up has reportedly started initial work on the Switch 2 port of the action title.
title: Stellar Blade's Nintendo Switch 2 Port Reportedly in Development After Successful PC Launch

description: Vivo X Fold 5 will weigh around 216g, and measure about 9.2mm in thickness when folded, a senior company official has revealed. It will be around 2mm thinner and 20g lighter than the current Vivo X Fold 3 Pro. The upcoming foldable will support 80W wired and 40W wireless fast charging, as well as reverse charging. The Vivo X Fold 5 will be backed by a 6,000mAh battery.
title: Vivo X Fold 5 Dimensions Confirmed Ahead of June 25 Launch; Charging Capacity Revealed

description: The Poco F7 5G will launch in select global markets, including India, on June 24. The phone will be available via Flipkart. It is confirmed to get a Snapdragon 8s Gen 4 SoC paired with 12GB of LPDDR5X RAM. The handset will be equipped with a 6,000sq mm vapour cooling chamber. The Indian variant will pack a 7,550mAh battery with 90W wired fast charging and 22.5W reverse wired charging support. It will sport an OIS-supported 50-megapixel dual rear camera unit.
title: Poco F7 5G Confirmed to Get Snapdragon 8s Gen 4 Chipset Ahead of June 24 Launch

description: Samsung's next-generation foldables have been part of several leaks and rumours for a while now. While Samsung is yet to reveal an official launch date, a new leak has surfaced online that suggests that the Galaxy Unpacked event for the Galaxy Z Fold 7 and Galaxy Z Flip 7 will take place on July 9. The event is rumoured to take place in New York.
title: Samsung Galaxy Unpacked Event for Galaxy Z Fold 7, Galaxy Z Flip 7 Tipped to Take Place on July 9

description: Facebook has announced passkeys as an alternative sign-in method for its app on Android and iOS devices. It enables users to verify their digital credentials in an easier and a more secure way. As per the company, passkeys on Facebook leverage the fingerprint, face or PIN that is used for unlocking the device, eliminating the need of memorising individual passwords.
title: Facebook Rolls Out Passkey Support for Easier and Secure Sign-In, Meta Pay Purchases

description: Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited (BSNL) announced the name of its 5G service via its social media handle on Wednesday. It is dubbed Q-5G, short for Quantum 5G. This move comes nearly a week after the state-owned telecommunications provider invited public input for naming its 5G services before it commences trial. Further, BSNL has also launched the Q-5G Fixed Wireless Access (FWA) service in select circles, promising “blazing fast” network speeds and a SIM-less operation.
title: BSNL Announces Q-5G Service in India, Launches SIM-Less Quantum 5G FWA for Enterprises in Select Circles

description: Extreme ultraviolet (EUV) lithography machines are the only such systems that can inscribe transistors smaller than 7nm on a microchip. This means everything from a modern smartphones, powerful GPUs, and data servers powering the compute for advanced AI models are all developed using this technology. And, there is only company in the world that manufactures these machines — ASML.
title: Netherland’s ASML Is the Most Important Company Behind the Global Rise of AI: 5 Things You Should Know
